00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:47,306
That’s right, the way they do at Princeton.
Come on, Mark.

228
00:17:47,425 --> 00:17:49,745
It’s gonna be fun. Come on, baby.

229
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:19,296
Did you bring your lunch?

230
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:30,012
”Miss Eileen Webster.” Ah!

231
00:19:08,881 --> 00:19:11,279
- Who’s fightin’ her?
- That’s Nakamura.

232
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:16,039
- He’s the one I met. He’s very famous.
- Is that Nakamura?

233
00:19:16,879 --> 00:19:20,477
It’s about a lady who turns into a lion.

234
00:19:20,597 --> 00:19:25,556
She gonna turn into a lion right here?
I wanna see that.

235
00:19:46,069 --> 00:19:49,267
I love you, Lloyd. I love you terribly.

236
00:19:49,387 --> 00:19:53,026
I always have and I guess I always will.

237
00:19:53,146 --> 00:19:55,107
I love you, honey.

238
00:19:56,146 --> 00:19:58,505
Awful glad you’re here, too.

239
00:20:07,183 --> 00:20:10,703
Everybody acting
like nobody ever kissed in the world.

240
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:51,969
She wouldn’t be half so ugly if she didn’t
stick her face in that flour barrel.

241
00:20:52,088 --> 00:20:54,210
She?

242
00:20:54,329 --> 00:20:56,288
Well, whatever.

243
00:20:57,208 --> 00:20:59,168
He had me.

244
00:21:06,284 --> 00:21:10,723
He’s a male actress. It says here
they’ve been trained since childhood

245
00:21:10,843 --> 00:21:13,722
to have the grace of a woman
and yet the power of a man.

246
00:21:13,843 --> 00:21:14,922
Oh, my word.

247
00:21:17,481 --> 00:21:19,520
My lord! That’s my father!

248
00:21:46,791 --> 00:21:49,630
Is he man enough now for you, Lloyd?

249
00:21:50,710 --> 00:21:52,669
Is that the same fellow?

250
00:21:52,789 --> 00:21:54,549
Uh-huh.

251
00:22:11,544 --> 00:22:14,343
It’s all right.

252
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:26,460
I am sure it must be very difficult

253
00:22:26,579 --> 00:22:30,218
to enjoy theatre
so different from your own.

254
00:22:30,338 --> 00:22:33,816
- We found it fascinating.
- I am glad.

255
00:22:34,856 --> 00:22:37,615
Kabuki’s very old, isn’t it?

256
00:22:37,735 --> 00:22:40,056
Some 300 years.

257
00:22:40,175 --> 00:22:44,054
I find myself becoming intrigued
by everything in Japan.

258
00:22:44,174 --> 00:22:50,011
I should be happy to help you know
my country better, if at any time I can.

259
00:22:50,931 --> 00:22:55,450
You did not enjoy the evening so much,
I fear, Major Gruver.

260
00:22:55,571 --> 00:22:58,610
Oh, yeah. I thought it was a fine play.

261
00:22:59,609 --> 00:23:05,247
I thought maybe you could use a Marilyn
Monroe here and there, you know, to...

262
00:23:07,247 --> 00:23:13,284
Unfortunately, Miss Monroes were barred
from kabuki in the 17th century.

263
00:23:14,604 --> 00:23:18,203
I didn’t mean to sound corny.
I just didn’t know what to say about it.

264
00:23:18,322 --> 00:23:20,642
Please, do not apologize.

265
00:23:20,762 --> 00:23:25,561
I am great admirer of Miss Monroe myself.

266
00:23:25,681 --> 00:23:28,919
That’s two of us. That’s you and me, boy.

267
00:23:32,999 --> 00:23:38,356
No, don’t do it to me. It’s real good.
Thank you very much. Why not?

268
00:23:38,476 --> 00:23:41,876
- Let’s go and see the garden.
- OK, you go on. I’ll take this.

269
00:23:43,516 --> 00:23:46,915
That’s fine, fine cooking. Very good.

270
00:23:54,673 --> 00:23:56,911
Here you are, honey.

271
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:59,990
- No, thank you.
- Don’t care for any?

272
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:04,149
- Sit down, darling.
- You look awful pretty.

273
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:10,868
I’ve been doing a lot of thinking
with you away, Lloyd.

274
00:24:10,988 --> 00:24:13,826
- Answer me one thing.
- What’s that, honey?

275
00:24:13,945 --> 00:24:16,305
Why aren’t we married now?

276
00:24:17,184 --> 00:24:20,984
- Isn’t that a silly question?
- No, not really.

277
00:24:21,103 --> 00:24:23,703
You do a lot of wondering in Tulsa.

278
00:24:23,823 --> 00:24:28,022
Well, I suppose the Korean War
might have a little something to do with it.

279
00:24:28,142 --> 00:24:31,580
Wasn’t Korea maybe convenient, Lloyd?

280
00:24:31,701 --> 00:24:32,780
Convenient?

281
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:39,137
What I really mean is... do I mean
everything to you as you do to me?

282
00:24:39,259 --> 00:24:40,817
Course you do, honey.

283
00:24:40,937 --> 00:24:44,457
I went to visit your mother
before I came here, there in Richmond.

284
00:24:44,576 --> 00:24:45,417
My mother?

285
00:24:45,537 --> 00:24:48,575
I was appalled at the loneliness
in which she lives,

286
00:24:48,695 --> 00:24:50,934
and the way your father’s content to go off

287
00:24:51,054 --> 00:24:53,374
and leave her walled up
in a circle of friends

288
00:24:53,494 --> 00:24:56,293
while he plunges off to the war.

289
00:24:56,412 --> 00:25:00,451
Hold on a second. You’ve got to
remember my father’s a general, honey.

290
00:25:00,571 --> 00:25:02,731
Besides, my mother
wants to live that way.

291
00:25:02,851 --> 00:25:05,330
- Don’t be ridiculous.
- Don’t tell me that.

292
00:25:05,450 --> 00:25:10,729
No woman wants to live any way except
body and soul with the man she loves.

293
00:25:10,849 --> 00:25:13,728
You’ll never tuck me away
in some little town.

294
00:25:13,848 --> 00:25:17,567
Become the greatest general
in air-force history, but love me too.

295
00:25:17,687 --> 00:25:20,525
But do I love you, baby. I do.

296
00:25:22,445 --> 00:25:28,803
Well, I guess all I’m trying to say is that -
and I really mean this, Lloyd -

297
00:25:28,923 --> 00:25:32,281
if what you want
is a family like our fathers have

298
00:25:32,401 --> 00:25:35,161
and promotion in the air force

299
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:39,119
and position in society
like our mothers have,

300
00:25:39,239 --> 00:25:45,798
and you marry me because I’m pretty and
smart and have guts and know the ropes...

301
00:25:47,997 --> 00:25:51,995
then I don’t think
you want to marry me, Lloyd.

302
00:25:52,116 --> 00:25:55,955
I’m sorry.
I guess I’ve been thinking too much.

303
00:25:57,435 --> 00:26:01,193
Yeah, I think you have
been thinking too much.

304
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:19,266
Now...

305
00:26:19,385 --> 00:26:21,425
Now quit it.

306
00:26:21,546 --> 00:26:25,585
OK. I don’t know.
Maybe things’ll turn out after all.

307
00:26:25,705 --> 00:26:28,704
What do you mean, maybe?
Sure, it’s gonna turn out.

308
00:26:28,824 --> 00:26:33,142
It’s just all that nonsense you talk about
every time we get together.

309
00:26:33,262 --> 00:26:36,902
Nonsense? I hadn’t realized
it was nonsense.

310
00:26:37,021 --> 00:26:39,661
Course it is, honey. It’s all very simple.

311
00:26:39,782 --> 00:26:41,580
Now, look here.

312
00:26:41,701 --> 00:26:46,577
I want a wife and a family.
I want a home in America.

313
00:26:46,697 --> 00:26:51,656
And every time I think of a home like that,
I think about it with a woman like you.

314
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:54,135
A girl with a good army
background like my own...

315
00:26:54,255 --> 00:26:58,614
What do you mean, a girl like me?
I’m not a type. I’m me.

316
00:26:58,734 --> 00:27:01,893
Lloyd, it’s me you’ve got to love.

317
00:27:02,572 --> 00:27:07,971
Haven’t you ever felt like grabbing me and
hauling me off to a shack somewhere?

318
00:27:08,091 --> 00:27:11,012
You know better than that.
Of course I have.

319
00:27:11,131 --> 00:27:14,489
- Then what’s holding you back?
- Eileen, are you ever gonna grow up?

320
00:27:14,611 --> 00:27:17,648
There’s a right time
and a wrong time to do things.

321
00:27:17,769 --> 00:27:22,207
You have responsibilities to other people.
You have a position to fulfill.

322
00:27:22,326 --> 00:27:26,126
- You’re not alone in this world.
- You defend yourself like a fort.

323
00:27:26,246 --> 00:27:31,004
No matter how I defend myself, you gotta
understand I am not in a position

324
00:27:31,124 --> 00:27:35,602
to be hauling my fiancée away
to a shack somewhere like an alley cat.

325
00:27:35,723 --> 00:27:37,801
I wasn’t brought up that way.

326
00:27:37,922 --> 00:27:40,362
You’re going to do everything
expected of you?

327
00:27:40,482 --> 00:27:42,641
I’m certainly gonna try.

328
00:27:42,761 --> 00:27:45,799
I don’t expect you to marry me
just because it’s expected of you.

329
00:27:45,919 --> 00:27:49,358
Sometimes I look at you
and I don’t understand you.

330
00:27:49,478 --> 00:27:55,237
I think sometimes I don’t even know
who you are or what you’re all about.

331
00:27:55,878 --> 00:27:58,837
Maybe you don’t. Maybe you never will.

332
00:28:14,431 --> 00:28:17,230
- …so long as you both shall live?
- I will.

333
00:28:17,350 --> 00:28:20,109
Katsumi, wilt though have this man
to thy wedded husband,

334
00:28:20,229 --> 00:28:23,668
to live together after God’s ordinance
in the holy state of matrimony,

335
00:28:23,787 --> 00:28:27,427
love him, comfort him, honor
and keep him, in sickness and in health,

336
00:28:27,548 --> 00:28:34,185
and forsaking all others keep thee only
unto him, so long as you both shall live?

337
00:28:36,024 --> 00:28:38,384
- She will.
- She will.

338
00:28:39,782 --> 00:28:43,822
If any man can show just cause why
they may not be lawfully joined together,

339
00:28:43,942 --> 00:28:47,741
let him now speak
or else hereafter for ever hold his peace.

340
00:28:54,378 --> 00:28:57,138
Do you realize
you waive all your legal rights?

341
00:28:57,258 --> 00:28:59,257
I signed all the papers, didn’t I?

342
00:28:59,376 --> 00:29:03,296
You’ll have to look after your wife on
your own. The air force is not responsible.

343
00:29:03,415 --> 00:29:06,775
Yeah, I know. Romantic, ain’t it, Major?

344
00:29:08,695 --> 00:29:11,933
Will you finish this ugly deed
and get it over?

345
00:29:12,053 --> 00:29:14,332
I pronounce you man and wife.
Sign over there.

346
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:16,412
Just a minute.

347
00:29:34,446 --> 00:29:38,404
That’s it, Mrs. Kelly. Just you and me now.

348
00:29:49,362 --> 00:29:51,681
Where do we sign?

349
00:29:51,801 --> 00:29:54,200
May as well witness this now, Major.

350
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,961
Yeah, all right.

351
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,519
It was a great honor meeting you,
Major Gruver.

352
00:30:00,639 --> 00:30:02,358
Thank you.

353
00:30:02,477 --> 00:30:07,836
Tell me, Consul, are all these ceremonies
conducted like this?

354
00:30:07,956 --> 00:30:11,836
Well, we do our best
to prevent as many as possible.

355
00:30:11,956 --> 00:30:16,713
We make the paperwork so difficult
that a good many of them lose steam.

356
00:30:16,833 --> 00:30:22,711
About how many GIs
have gone through this ceremony?

357
00:30:24,670 --> 00:30:27,311
About... 10,000.

358
00:30:28,071 --> 00:30:31,629
10,000? Well, then,
you let a few slip by you, didn’t you?

359
00:30:31,749 --> 00:30:33,708
A few, yes.

360
00:30:35,348 --> 00:30:37,426
How’s your girl, Major?

361
00:30:37,547 --> 00:30:40,226
Eileen? I haven’t seen her
in a couple of days.

362
00:30:40,347 --> 00:30:42,986
I’ve been moving in,
getting my things arranged.

363
00:30:43,106 --> 00:30:48,183
She’s been hightailing it
with the brass, socializing.

364
00:30:49,303 --> 00:30:52,182
Major, ain’t you gonna kiss the bride?

365
00:30:53,821 --> 00:30:56,380
Sure, I’m gonna kiss the bride.

366
00:30:57,060 --> 00:30:59,419
Yeah. Sure.

367
00:31:00,379 --> 00:31:05,017
Listen, I want you to take good care
of this boy, you hear?

368
00:31:07,736 --> 00:31:11,376
Here’s your ticket, honey. Don’t forget it.

369
00:31:12,695 --> 00:31:14,335
OK, boy.

370
00:31:16,014 --> 00:31:19,413
Thanks, Major. Took a lot of guts
for you to come here today.

371
00:31:19,533 --> 00:31:20,492
Quit.

372
00:31:20,612 --> 00:31:25,450
If you ever need a job done that you West
Point guys ain’t allowed to do yourselves,

373
00:31:25,571 --> 00:31:26,892
I’m your man.

374
00:31:27,012 --> 00:31:31,050
- I’m gonna call on you.
- Come on, let’s get a belt.

375
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:34,329
- How are you, Lloyd?
- Fine, just fine.

376
00:31:34,450 --> 00:31:37,007
- That’s a pretty dress you got on.
- Thanks.

377
00:31:37,127 --> 00:31:39,326
Lloyd, sit down, son.

378
00:31:39,446 --> 00:31:41,406
All righty.

379
00:31:43,925 --> 00:31:48,844
- Thank you for coming over so promptly.
- That’s all right. I was just darning socks.

380
00:31:49,364 --> 00:31:51,523
Lloyd...

381
00:31:51,643 --> 00:31:57,282
I don’t exactly know how to put this.
It’s a little embarrassing. For me, that is.

382
00:31:57,402 --> 00:32:00,520
You were a witness
at a marriage yesterday between...

383
00:32:00,641 --> 00:32:03,839
one of your men and a Japanese girl.

384
00:32:04,679 --> 00:32:08,238
Yeah, one of the men
from my outfit in Korea.

385
00:32:08,357 --> 00:32:14,197
You realize, of course, there’s an army
policy to discourage all such marriages.

386
00:32:14,277 --> 00:32:19,993
I think they couldn’t have been
discouraged. They’re very much in love.

387
00:32:20,114 --> 00:32:25,632
I dare say. However, you personally
seemed to sanction the marriage...

388
00:32:25,753 --> 00:32:29,072
No, I didn’t mean
to give that impression at all.

389
00:32:29,192 --> 00:32:32,711
I didn’t sanction it.
I tried to talk him out of it before.

390
00:32:32,831 --> 00:32:36,670
But, Lloyd, darling,
you did act as his witness.

391
00:32:36,790 --> 00:32:39,747
Well, as long as
it was gonna be inevitable,

392
00:32:39,867 --> 00:32:42,668
I thought I might as well
try to make it pleasant.

393
00:32:42,788 --> 00:32:45,028
Don’t you see the position
that puts me in?

394
00:32:45,147 --> 00:32:47,866
Since I’m the area commander here...

395
00:32:47,985 --> 00:32:52,785
You didn’t do anything to encourage
this marriage, sir. I did all this on my own.

396
00:32:52,904 --> 00:32:56,705
What do you mean?
On your own, Lloyd, dear?

397
00:32:56,824 --> 00:33:01,782
Everything you do reflects on the general.
After all, he is Eileen’s father.

398
00:33:01,901 --> 00:33:04,420
This places me
in a position of incompetence

399
00:33:04,541 --> 00:33:08,779
when it comes to doing anything
to help my own men.

400
00:33:08,899 --> 00:33:13,378
Let’s stop beating around the bush.
What’s wrong between you and Eileen?

401
00:33:13,498 --> 00:33:17,137
You haven’t been to see her
for several days.

402
00:33:20,177 --> 00:33:25,654
Well... you talked about
being embarrassed, sir, before.

403
00:33:25,774 --> 00:33:28,054
I’m embarrassed too.

404
00:33:28,174 --> 00:33:31,813
- What about?
- About my whole situation here.

405
00:33:31,933 --> 00:33:35,652
I’m a pilot, sir. I was doing a job in Korea.
An unfinished job.

406
00:33:35,772 --> 00:33:37,770
I’m pulled off that job and sent here

407
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:42,010
and plonked down at a desk
at this inter-service whatever it is.

408
00:33:42,130 --> 00:33:45,407
As far as I can see,
there’s absolutely nothing to do.

409
00:33:45,528 --> 00:33:47,647
All so’s I can be with Eileen.

410
00:33:47,767 --> 00:33:51,806
There’s nothing dishonest about it.
That is, if you plan to get married.

411
00:33:51,926 --> 00:33:56,805
- I think I know how Lloyd feels.
- Do you plan to get married or not?

412
00:33:56,925 --> 00:34:00,684
- Really, dear.
- I’m her mother. I want to know.

413
00:34:02,523 --> 00:34:08,441
Well, Mrs. Webster, as of the moment,
Eileen isn’t too sure about it and I...

414
00:34:08,561 --> 00:34:14,640
We know, Lloyd, dear. There’s evidently
been some slight strain between you two,

415
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:17,479
but don’t let it become too important.

416
00:34:17,599 --> 00:34:22,237
This is Sunday night. Why don’t you
call her up later and ask her out to dinner?

417
00:34:22,357 --> 00:34:23,517
Well...

418
00:34:23,637 --> 00:34:27,036
Mother, I found the dearest little shop...

419
00:34:27,156 --> 00:34:30,034
- Hi, Lloyd.
- Hello, Eileen.

420
00:34:30,154 --> 00:34:32,513
Lloyd just came in to see you.

421
00:34:32,633 --> 00:34:34,634
Oh?

422
00:34:35,713 --> 00:34:37,671
Listen...

423
00:34:38,631 --> 00:34:41,591
I thought... It’s Sunday night
and I thought maybe

424
00:34:41,711 --> 00:34:47,510
you and I can go out and catch a movie
or something, if you feel like it.

425
00:34:47,630 --> 00:34:51,188
I’m sorry, Lloyd. I’m having dinner
with some friends tonight.

426
00:34:51,308 --> 00:34:54,187
Well, what about tomorrow?

427
00:34:55,467 --> 00:34:57,426
That’s booked too, I’m afraid.

428
00:35:00,305 --> 00:35:04,943
Well, it looks as though
I’m holding pretty tough cards.

429
00:35:06,383 --> 00:35:09,182
What about next week?

430
00:35:10,341 --> 00:35:12,501
Of course, Lloyd. Call me.

431
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:17,219
OK.

432
00:35:19,499 --> 00:35:21,779
Mrs. Webster, General.

433
00:35:21,899 --> 00:35:23,858
- Goodbye, Lloyd.
- Goodbye, Eileen.

434
00:35:23,978 --> 00:35:25,937
Goodbye, Lloyd.

435
00:35:31,814 --> 00:35:35,973
Eileen, why did you tell him
you were busy tonight?

436
00:35:37,493 --> 00:35:41,172
Because I don’t want to see Lloyd Gruver
when you ask him to see me.

437
00:35:41,292 --> 00:35:46,731
Besides, I do have a date with that young
lieutenant and his wife from Fort Bragg.

438
00:35:46,851 --> 00:35:48,810
A whole bunch of us.

439
00:35:55,126 --> 00:35:57,886
I hope you don’t lose my man for me.

440
00:36:18,681 --> 00:36:21,639
Give me a martini, will you?

441
00:36:22,319 --> 00:36:24,279
No, make it a lemonade.

442
00:36:25,598 --> 00:36:27,958
No, give me a scotch and soda.

443
00:36:28,598 --> 00:36:31,875
- Scotch and soda.
- Scotch and soda, sir.

444
00:36:31,997 --> 00:36:36,954
There’s such a thing as insolence
through manner, you know.

445
00:36:41,633 --> 00:36:45,112
I hate to admit it,
but I guess that’s what I said.

446
00:36:46,551 --> 00:36:51,910
I thought it sounded kinda strange coming
from a guy who shot down nine MiGs.

447
00:36:52,030 --> 00:36:55,228
That’s a kind of reflex action.
I’m a West Point man, you know.

448
00:36:55,348 --> 00:36:57,988
I guess it sneaks out sometimes.

449
00:37:01,107 --> 00:37:06,185
So listen, Captain, what does a fella
do round here after the sun goes down?

450
00:37:06,305 --> 00:37:08,785
Why? You on the loose?

451
00:37:10,064 --> 00:37:11,825
Halfway.

452
00:37:11,945 --> 00:37:14,422
Bring him another.

453
00:37:14,542 --> 00:37:17,581
What part of the south are you from?

454
00:37:17,701 --> 00:37:21,820
Almost any old place
that’s got an army post on it.

455
