01:04:53,208 --> 01:04:57,167
Hana-ogi-san.
This is a great day for our house.

684
01:04:58,966 --> 01:05:00,926
Major Gruver-san.

685
01:05:03,805 --> 01:05:05,764
How do you do, Miss Ogi?

686
01:05:07,684 --> 01:05:11,923
- Where you going?
- I gotta help Katsumi with the...

687
01:05:16,242 --> 01:05:21,520
It looks as though everybody’s ran off
and left us alone here.

688
01:05:21,639 --> 01:05:25,679
Certainly was nice of you
to come over here this evening, Miss Ogi.

689
01:05:25,799 --> 01:05:31,158
I was just tickled to death
when they told me you were coming over.

690
01:05:32,478 --> 01:05:34,437
I’ll just sit down here.

691
01:05:38,156 --> 01:05:40,117
Well, Miss Ogi.

692
01:05:41,476 --> 01:05:43,835
Let me fix you a little drink.

693
01:05:44,794 --> 01:05:47,754
No, not... Well, OK.

694
01:05:54,472 --> 01:05:56,432
Here’s to you.

695
01:05:58,511 --> 01:06:03,830
It’s good. Don’t tell me. I know you’ve got
to slosh this around in here a little bit

696
01:06:03,950 --> 01:06:08,268
and get the dribble off
and give it right back to you.

697
01:06:08,388 --> 01:06:10,348
Now you take that.

698
01:06:12,947 --> 01:06:14,907
All right.

699
01:06:19,106 --> 01:06:22,626
I was surprised to find
that they make that stuff out of rice.

700
01:06:22,746 --> 01:06:25,663
We have rice back home in America.

701
01:06:25,784 --> 01:06:29,464
We just make rice pudding out of it.
We don’t drink it.

702
01:06:29,584 --> 01:06:33,142
This is the first liquid rice I’ve ran into.

703
01:06:41,500 --> 01:06:43,460
You know, did...

704
01:06:44,619 --> 01:06:49,538
Did anyone ever tell you, Miss Ogi,
that you’re a fine-looking woman?

705
01:06:49,658 --> 01:06:51,618
I mean, really fine.

706
01:06:53,298 --> 01:06:58,856
You’re even better looking offstage
than you are on. That’s the truth.

707
01:06:58,976 --> 01:07:02,295
You get up there and sing,
dance, act, everything.

708
01:07:02,415 --> 01:07:04,454
You’re all-round great.

709
01:07:10,574 --> 01:07:15,732
I wonder where Kelly and Katsumi...
I’m getting kinda hungry again.

710
01:07:20,850 --> 01:07:22,810
Look, Miss Ogi...

711
01:07:24,409 --> 01:07:29,687
I’m not up to Japanese ways of doing
things. Maybe I’m saying the wrong thing.

712
01:07:29,808 --> 01:07:33,687
Maybe my American manners
are embarrassing.

713
01:07:33,807 --> 01:07:36,206
But I figured,
as you came over here tonight,

714
01:07:36,326 --> 01:07:39,246
maybe you were interested
a little bit in meeting me too.

715
01:07:39,366 --> 01:07:46,884
Maybe I’m wrong, but if I’m wrong, then
you got to tell me where we go from here.

716
01:07:47,604 --> 01:07:51,563
Cos I don’t know what to say.
I’m runnin’ out of things to say.

717
01:07:55,242 --> 01:08:01,639
My father was killed by American bomb
dropped on my country.

718
01:08:03,080 --> 01:08:05,439
You have been my enemy.

719
01:08:07,477 --> 01:08:09,958
I have hated Americans.

720
01:08:10,077 --> 01:08:12,837
I have thought they are savages.

721
01:08:14,236 --> 01:08:17,796
There has been nothing
but vengeance in my heart.

722
01:08:17,916 --> 01:08:23,473
Miss Ogi, there were an awful lot
of Americans that were killed too.

723
01:08:24,873 --> 01:08:28,234
I think it would be best
if we forgot about that.

724
01:08:29,912 --> 01:08:33,471
You have been watching me at the bridge.

725
01:08:33,592 --> 01:08:35,552
Watching me dance.

726
01:08:37,150 --> 01:08:40,510
Watching me
as I go back to the dormitory.

727
01:08:41,990 --> 01:08:44,748
But I have been watching you too.

728
01:08:46,188 --> 01:08:49,547
And you have not looked like a savage.

729
01:08:50,427 --> 01:08:53,466
And when Katsumi-san told me
how gently you kissed her

730
01:08:53,586 --> 01:08:56,745
the day she became a bride,

731
01:08:56,865 --> 01:09:00,825
how tenderly you kissed
my sweet little friend,

732
01:09:02,263 --> 01:09:05,504
I realized the hate was of my own making.

733
01:09:07,584 --> 01:09:11,902
That is why I came
to ask you to forgive me

734
01:09:12,022 --> 01:09:14,381
for what I have been feeling.

735
01:09:16,341 --> 01:09:19,061
Gruver-san, will you forgive me?

736
01:09:23,499 --> 01:09:27,138
You make me feel
like an awful fool, Miss Ogi.

737
01:09:29,297 --> 01:09:33,096
I really feel that
I oughta ask you to forgive me

738
01:09:33,216 --> 01:09:38,055
for some of the things that...
I’ve been thinking.

739
01:09:41,294 --> 01:09:46,334
I come from the north of Japan
and my father was a farmer.

740
01:09:46,454 --> 01:09:49,052
There were nine children.

741
01:09:49,172 --> 01:09:51,771
And we were very poor.

742
01:09:51,891 --> 01:09:55,771
There are too many people
in my crowded country.

743
01:09:55,891 --> 01:09:59,170
I took the examination at Matsubayashi

744
01:09:59,290 --> 01:10:01,851
and now I am first dancer of all.

745
01:10:03,409 --> 01:10:07,767
When I’m too old to dance,
I will become head teacher.

746
01:10:10,167 --> 01:10:12,885
My life is planned.

747
01:10:13,005 --> 01:10:16,165
I am dedicated to Matsubayashi,

748
01:10:16,286 --> 01:10:20,245
as you are dedicated
to American military life.

749
01:10:22,564 --> 01:10:25,123
I have never been in love...

750
01:10:26,244 --> 01:10:30,322
but I have dreamed and thought about it...

751
01:10:31,401 --> 01:10:33,362
and waited.

752
01:10:36,241 --> 01:10:40,760
The danger that lies ahead of us,
we must face now.

753
01:10:43,000 --> 01:10:46,159
The danger of discovery for both of us.

754
01:10:47,759 --> 01:10:52,116
The danger of weakness when it is over.

755
01:10:58,995 --> 01:11:01,554
I will never fall in love again.

756
01:11:03,634 --> 01:11:09,593
But I will love you, if that is your desire.

757
01:11:49,702 --> 01:11:51,663
How do you do?

758
01:11:55,381 --> 01:11:57,860
- Miss Webster.
- Hello.

759
01:11:59,781 --> 01:12:02,978
- Mr. Nakamura, how nice of you to come.
- It is a great pleasure.

760
01:12:03,099 --> 01:12:05,898
And may I say that you look
especially beautiful today.

761
01:12:06,018 --> 01:12:08,579
I haven’t been
to this month’s kabuki programme.

762
01:12:08,699 --> 01:12:11,298
I know. You see, I have been waiting.

763
01:12:11,418 --> 01:12:14,856
- Eileen.
- Mother, you remember Mr. Nakamura.

764
01:12:14,976 --> 01:12:17,575
- How do you do, Mrs. Webster?
- Yes, of course.

765
01:12:17,695 --> 01:12:20,134
This party isn’t given especially for you.

766
01:12:20,255 --> 01:12:24,014
You’ve got to circulate around
and cement Japanese-American relations.

767
01:12:24,134 --> 01:12:27,773
That’s exactly what
Mr. Nakamura and I are doing.

768
01:12:27,893 --> 01:12:32,972
Nakamura-san, my little girl wants
your autograph. She admires you so.

769
01:12:33,092 --> 01:12:37,650
- Of course. Will you please excuse me?
- Yes, of course.

770
01:12:39,651 --> 01:12:41,809
Has Lloyd come yet?

771
01:12:41,929 --> 01:12:44,568
How many weeks
are you gonna keep on pretending?

772
01:12:44,688 --> 01:12:48,807
- Lloyd is not coming.
- I’m absolutely furious at him.

773
01:12:48,927 --> 01:12:52,925
How can he ignore the general’s
invitation? I had it delivered to his office.

774
01:12:53,045 --> 01:12:57,204
I’m stuck with that Farrington woman.
Can you help me out?

775
01:12:58,724 --> 01:13:03,603
Uh-oh. There’s Crawford. Whenever
he shows up, there’s always something.

776
01:13:03,723 --> 01:13:06,482
Can I speak to you alone
for a minute, General?

777
01:13:06,603 --> 01:13:11,681
Major, do you have that list with you?
I want to see if the Williams have come.

778
01:13:11,801 --> 01:13:13,200
Yes, they have.

779
01:13:15,160 --> 01:13:17,119
Waiter. Could you leave?

780
01:13:21,079 --> 01:13:25,477
The reason I took this up with you
is because it concerns Major Gruver.

781
01:13:25,598 --> 01:13:29,037
We think he’s hooked
onto a Japanese dame.

782
01:13:29,157 --> 01:13:31,836
I’m sorry, but this thing’s
gotten me all riled up.

783
01:13:31,956 --> 01:13:34,717
Do you realize what it’ll mean
to the enlisted men

784
01:13:34,836 --> 01:13:37,874
if they find out that their big hero,
Ace Gruver, is out with...

785
01:13:37,995 --> 01:13:42,313
I’ve known Major Gruver all his life.
I’m a close friend of his father’s.

786
01:13:42,433 --> 01:13:45,712
- I assure you, you must be wrong.
- He was seen going into that house.

787
01:13:45,832 --> 01:13:48,990
My men have been watching
a troublemaker named Kelly.

788
01:13:49,111 --> 01:13:53,591
- He’s shacked up with another native...
- Kelly’s married to a Japanese girl.

789
01:13:53,711 --> 01:13:57,751
Major Gruver was the best man. It seems
quite natural to me that he’d visit them.

790
01:13:57,870 --> 01:14:00,828
- How am I gonna handle the situation?
- Don’t handle it.

791
01:14:00,948 --> 01:14:03,387
I trust Major Gruver implicitly.

792
01:14:03,508 --> 01:14:06,428
Is it all right with you if I post an order

793
01:14:06,547 --> 01:14:12,065
to keep these officers from being seen
with indigenous personnel?

794
01:14:12,185 --> 01:14:14,466
If they are seen,
there’s something we can do.

795
01:14:14,586 --> 01:14:15,706
All right.

796
01:14:38,340 --> 01:14:39,539
Lloyd.

797
01:15:00,774 --> 01:15:03,133
No one saw you come?

798
01:15:03,253 --> 01:15:08,092
No, there’s no military personnel
around here. Except me.

799
01:15:10,051 --> 01:15:13,810
- We must go to the tea ceremony.
- Yeah, I know.

800
01:15:14,930 --> 01:15:16,890
Good afternoon.

801
01:15:22,248 --> 01:15:25,807
All this getting up and down like to kill me.

802
01:15:56,800 --> 01:16:00,239
He makes such a production
of everything.

803
01:16:01,598 --> 01:16:04,758
The pleasure does not lie in the end itself.

804
01:16:04,878 --> 01:16:07,997
It’s the pleasurable steps to that end.

805
01:16:08,117 --> 01:16:10,076
I see.

806
01:16:36,910 --> 01:16:39,349
- That you, Ace?
- Yeah, Kelly.

807
01:16:40,229 --> 01:16:43,389
- Come on in here.
- I can’t right now.

808
01:16:44,908 --> 01:16:48,027
He’d be surprised you come in this way.

809
01:16:48,147 --> 01:16:50,426
He’d faint.

810
01:16:50,546 --> 01:16:54,346
Just a little lower, Katsumi.
You always seem to be a little above it.

811
01:16:54,466 --> 01:16:56,665
Yeah, that’s it. Yeah, yeah.

812
01:17:07,222 --> 01:17:09,461
Kelly-san, now you get in tub?

813
01:17:09,582 --> 01:17:11,540
OK, all right.

814
01:17:12,740 --> 01:17:16,939
- Is Hana-ogi coming over tonight?
- Yeah, if she can get away.

815
01:17:17,059 --> 01:17:23,019
We gonna cook up some fine St Louis
goulash with a little Memphis greens.

816
01:17:26,697 --> 01:17:30,696
What are you doing tonight after dinner
when Hana-ogi goes back to the theatre?

817
01:17:30,816 --> 01:17:32,175
" Nothing.

818
01:17:32,295 --> 01:17:34,774
How about playing poker
with Katsumi and me?

819
01:17:34,894 --> 01:17:39,134
" I’d be delighted
to take your money, and your pants.

820
01:17:41,053 --> 01:17:43,891
This is the life, ain’t it, Ace?

821
01:18:20,243 --> 01:18:22,203
There you are.

822
01:18:27,081 --> 01:18:29,041
How d’you do?

823
01:18:41,358 --> 01:18:43,677
I got one word for you.

824
01:18:43,798 --> 01:18:46,156
- What is that?
- Food.

825
01:18:58,793 --> 01:19:03,232
# Sayonara

826
01:19:03,353 --> 01:19:07,632
# Japanese goodbye

827
01:19:07,752 --> 01:19:12,469
# Whisper “Sayonara”

828
01:19:12,589 --> 01:19:16,468
# Lover, don’t you cry

829
01:19:17,668 --> 01:19:22,307
# No more we stop to see

830
01:19:22,427 --> 01:19:25,946
# Pretty cherry blossom

831
01:19:27,186 --> 01:19:31,906
# No more we ‘neath the tree

832
01:19:32,025 --> 01:19:35,544
# Looking at the sky

833
01:19:36,545 --> 01:19:41,063
# Sayonara

834
01:19:41,582 --> 01:19:46,261
# Sayonara

835
01:19:46,381 --> 01:19:51,140
# Goodbye

836
01:19:54,459 --> 01:19:57,298
That’s the cutest thing I ever saw, honey.

837
01:19:57,418 --> 01:19:59,377
I must go.

838
01:20:00,778 --> 01:20:03,657
Ooh! Good eatin’.

839
01:20:05,296 --> 01:20:06,256
Bye-bye.

840
01:20:06,376 --> 01:20:09,695
Are you going back
to the officers’ quarters tonight?

841
01:20:09,815 --> 01:20:12,895
No, I think I’m gonna just
fool around here.

842
01:20:13,014 --> 01:20:15,214
What will you do all evening?

843
01:20:15,334 --> 01:20:18,814
What am I gonna do?
I’m gonna get some beer, pretzels, girls.

844
01:20:18,934 --> 01:20:21,172
I’m gonna have a little fun for a change.

845
01:20:21,293 --> 01:20:24,332
Good. I don’t like you to be lonely.

846
01:20:30,171 --> 01:20:32,131
Take care.

847
01:20:55,043 --> 01:20:57,003
Come on in, Katsumi.

848
01:21:01,203 --> 01:21:04,482
I’m sorry, Lloyd.
I had to come. It’s important.

849
01:21:04,602 --> 01:21:06,561
Hello, Eileen.

850
01:21:09,761 --> 01:21:12,320
How are you?

851
01:21:12,441 --> 01:21:14,959
Sit down, will you?

852
01:21:15,079 --> 01:21:19,758
I’ll take this stuff out the way.
I was just gettin’ a little...

853
01:21:28,561 --> 01:21:30,316
Sit down here.

854
01:21:34,254 --> 01:21:35,628
How are you?

855
01:21:44,178 --> 01:21:47,737
- They’re after you, Lloyd.
- Who’s after me?

856
01:21:47,857 --> 01:21:51,536
There’s a colonel. His name’s Crawford.

857
01:21:51,656 --> 01:21:53,616
Oh, yeah.

858
01:21:55,054 --> 01:21:57,095
I know him.

859
01:21:57,215 --> 01:22:00,612
He’s the one that’s riding Kelly.
This is Kelly’s house.

860
01:22:00,732 --> 01:22:02,691
Yes, I know.

861
01:22:04,691 --> 01:22:09,168
- You want to hear this, don’t you, Lloyd?
- Yeah, sure. Course I do.

862
01:22:09,288 --> 01:22:14,726
I overheard Colonel Crawford say
that he’s been having this house watched,

863
01:22:14,846 --> 01:22:19,925
hoping to catch Kelly
at something irregular, I suppose.

864
01:22:20,044 --> 01:22:22,483
Anyhow, that’s how I knew where it was.

865
01:22:22,603 --> 01:22:27,922
Well, then they... they’ve seen me
coming in and out of here.

866
01:22:28,042 --> 01:22:30,001
Yes.

867
01:22:31,881 --> 01:22:34,719
I just felt that I had to tell you...

868
01:22:39,917 --> 01:22:41,877
Eileen...

869
01:22:43,315 --> 01:22:45,434
There’s something that I feel that...

870
01:22:45,554 --> 01:22:53,032
I must go, Lloyd. I just wanted to warn you
to be particularly careful about...

871
01:22:53,152 --> 01:22:55,111
About what, honey?

872
01:22:57,790 --> 01:23:02,028
About sticking strictly
to military regulations.

873
01:23:02,148 --> 01:23:05,188
Lloyd, they’ll do anything
to hang something on you,

874
01:23:05,307 --> 01:23:07,267
to keep you in line.

875
01:23:09,586 --> 01:23:14,024
After all, you’re the air force’s
pin-up boy, you know.

876
01:23:16,064 --> 01:23:20,222
Colonel Crawford sounded
as if he was after blood.

877
01:23:24,420 --> 01:23:30,258
- More than anything I could think of...
- I must go now, Lloyd. Good luck.

878
01:23:30,378 --> 01:23:33,216
Wait a minute. Let me help you.

879
01:23:35,416 --> 01:23:37,415
Eileen, I know...

880
01:23:37,495 --> 01:23:44,053
Lloyd, you’ve really thought seriously
about what you’re doing, haven’t you?

881
01:23:46,453 --> 01:23:48,811
Yes, I...

882
01:23:48,931 --> 01:23:50,851
I think I have.

883
01:23:50,971 --> 01:23:52,930
I hope so.

884
01:23:54,730 --> 01:23:59,248
You’ve a brilliant record in the air force.
People depend upon you.

885
01:23:59,368 --> 01:24:04,925
Before you throw all that you’ve worked
for away, be sure. Please be sure.

886
01:24:08,203 --> 01:24:14,801
Eileen, I don’t think if I had a million years
that I could tell you how all this happened.

887
01:24:17,800 --> 01:24:20,399
I’d better go before I lose all my charm.

888
01:24:48,349 --> 01:24:51,267
Do you like this old curious play?

889
01:24:52,708 --> 01:24:56,386
Yeah, I’m beginning to get a kick out of it.

890
01:25:02,464 --> 01:25:05,503
- See the rope between the rocks?
- Yeah.

891
01:25:05,623 --> 01:25:08,902
That is a Shinto sign
showing they are married.

892
01:25:09,022 --> 01:25:11,021
- What, the rocks?
- Yes.

893
01:25:11,140 --> 01:25:15,259
They’ve been together so long, our people
thought it was time they got married.

894
01:25:15,379 --> 01:25:20,778
- They look well together, don’t you think?
- Yeah. Make a handsome little couple.

895
01:25:20,898 --> 01:25:22,737
Do you like my country?

896
01:25:22,857 --> 01:25:26,695
Yeah, was all these funny things here
before when I came through Japan?

897
01:25:26,815 --> 01:25:28,775
Yes.

898
01:25:38,170 --> 01:25:41,289
- Well, hello.
- Hello there, double-double ugly.

899
01:25:41,410 --> 01:25:43,929
To what do we owe
the honor of this visit?

900
01:25:44,049 --> 01:25:48,887
Laundry. Gonna put down the dirties
and pick up the cleans.

901
01:25:52,206 --> 01:25:54,924
I hope you know what you’re doing.

902
01:25:55,044 --> 01:25:57,404
This came in.
Thought you might like to see it.

903
01:25:57,524 --> 01:26:01,882
”This is a routine reminder of
the recent orders issued by Camp Kobe:”

904
01:26:02,002 --> 01:26:05,441
”Any public display of affection
for a Japanese national

905
01:26:05,560 --> 01:26:07,760
by a member of this command
is forbidden.”

906
01:26:07,880 --> 01:26:10,519
”Officers should not even
appear on public streets

907
01:26:10,638 --> 01:26:14,076
accompanied by indigenous
female personnel.”

908
01:26:14,196 --> 01:26:18,035
- Hooray for Christmas.
- This is serious. Everybody got one.

909
01:26:18,156 --> 01:26:21,834
Listen, fool, Hana-ogi and I
are just as careful as we can be.

910
01:26:21,954 --> 01:26:25,833
We never go anyplace where we’re gonna
be seen by anybody that matters.

911
01:26:25,953 --> 01:26:28,712
We don’t even walk down the same street.

912
01:26:28,832 --> 01:26:32,111
We just go out in the country
and fool around.

913
01:26:32,231 --> 01:26:35,749
You’ve never been to the country
around here, have you?

914
01:26:35,869 --> 01:26:38,989
Awful pretty country round here. I mean it.

915
01:26:39,669 --> 01:26:43,787
You know what I saw yesterday?
I saw two rocks that just got married.

916
01:26:43,907 --> 01:26:47,225
- You what?
- I saw two rocks that got married.

917
01:26:47,345 --> 01:26:50,784
- And they looked very happy together too.
- I’ll bet they did.

918
01:26:50,904 --> 01:26:56,220
They did. If you were gonna be smart,
I’ll tell you what you’d do.

919
01:26:56,340 --> 01:26:58,660
You’d get your shoes shined
and go out tonight,

920
01:26:58,780 --> 01:27:01,498
cos tonight is gonna be Tanabata.

921
01:27:02,299 --> 01:27:04,257
OK, what’s Tanabata?

922
01:27:05,336 --> 01:27:09,175
You’re gonna sit there and tell me
you don’t know what Tanabata is?

923
01:27:09,296 --> 01:27:10,695
Yeah.

924
01:27:10,815 --> 01:27:13,054
My word, boy. I’m ashamed of you.

925
01:27:13,174 --> 01:27:15,734
I thought everybody knew
what Tanabata was.

926
01:27:15,854 --> 01:27:18,413
Tanabata is the night of love.

927
01:27:18,533 --> 01:27:20,851
You told me all about it one time.

928
01:27:20,971 --> 01:27:26,050
You were telling me about Harry Truman
and New York Yankees and sex,

929
01:27:26,170 --> 01:27:29,129
and New York Yankees
and Harry Truman and sex.

930
01:27:47,561 --> 01:27:50,880
What have I done
to deserve such happiness?

931
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:56,278
I have seen this night of Tanabata
come and go many times,

932
01:27:56,398 --> 01:28:00,437
but never before
have I understood what it meant.

933
01:28:01,477 --> 01:28:03,915
Tanabata.

934
01:28:04,035 --> 01:28:06,995
My heart is so full of love for you.

935
01:28:49,339 --> 01:28:51,298
- Miss Webster?
- Yes?

936
01:28:51,418 --> 01:28:55,336
Nakamura-san get your note.
Here is reply.

937
01:28:55,456 --> 01:28:59,335
He wishes if you will have dinner
with him and his guests.

938
01:28:59,455 --> 01:29:01,414
Thank you very much.

939
01:29:29,804 --> 01:29:34,762
They have a rather pleasant
garden here, Miss Webster.

940
01:29:36,162 --> 01:29:39,761
- Would you like to see it?
- Yes, I think I would.

941
01:30:03,232 --> 01:30:05,591
How beautiful.

942
01:30:13,467 --> 01:30:16,307
What are you really afraid of,
Miss Webster?

943
01:30:16,427 --> 01:30:21,984
You don’t think it would enter Major
Gruver’s mind to marry a Japanese girl?

944
01:30:23,664 --> 01:30:25,623
I don’t know.

945
01:30:25,742 --> 01:30:28,261
Then permit me to reassure you.

946
01:30:28,382 --> 01:30:33,659
I think Major Gruver is brave,
but not brave enough to face the censure

947
01:30:33,779 --> 01:30:36,498
that would result from such a marriage.

948
01:30:36,618 --> 01:30:40,537
As for our famous, honored Hana-ogi,

949
01:30:40,657 --> 01:30:44,456
there are many Japanese -
most of them, in fact -

950
01:30:44,575 --> 01:30:46,775
who look upon marriage to an Occidental

951
01:30:46,896 --> 01:30:50,934
with as much distaste
as your people do to one of us.

952
01:30:52,013 --> 01:30:54,613
I do not feel that way,

953
01:30:54,732 --> 01:30:58,132
but then I have had the privilege
of traveling in your country

954
01:30:58,252 --> 01:31:01,890
and knowing some great people there.

955
01:31:02,010 --> 01:31:05,689
And I am especially conscious
at this moment

956
01:31:05,809 --> 01:31:10,726
that beauty is not confined
to any one race.

957
01:31:14,165 --> 01:31:16,403
Do not turn away, Miss Webster.

958
01:31:16,523 --> 01:31:21,563
I am not necessarily making love to you.

959
01:31:24,681 --> 01:31:29,239
I am only stating a very obvious fact.

960
01:31:31,517 --> 01:31:34,157
May I see you again, Miss Webster,

961
01:31:34,277 --> 01:31:37,876
and acquaint you with more Japan?

962
01:31:38,875 --> 01:31:40,634
Of course.

963
01:31:40,754 --> 01:31:45,154
I need to know more, much more,
about everything.

964
01:32:05,345 --> 01:32:07,304
There she is.

965
01:32:09,144 --> 01:32:11,102
Hello, honey.

966
01:32:22,659 --> 01:32:24,619
Are you tired?

967
01:32:26,698 --> 01:32:31,654
No, I just been lying here
thinking about myself.

968
01:32:32,774 --> 01:32:35,413
I can’t believe I’m really here.

969
01:32:36,373 --> 01:32:40,452
It’s hard to believe
me being the same Lloyd Gruver

970
01:32:40,572 --> 01:32:44,531
that came over from Korea
just a little bit ago.

971
01:32:47,049 --> 01:32:52,807
I’ve been thinking
that all my life I’ve been so busy...

972
01:32:53,727 --> 01:32:56,567
snapping to and giving orders
and taking orders

973
01:32:56,686 --> 01:33:01,924
and being a general’s son
and doing the job and all that,

974
01:33:02,044 --> 01:33:05,802
I just never took time
to sit right down and...

975
01:33:07,122 --> 01:33:11,281
you know, think about
what my reason for living is.

976
01:33:13,799 --> 01:33:17,678
And I’ve been spending
some afternoons here just...

977
01:33:17,798 --> 01:33:22,236
bein’ peaceful and easy and thinking.

978
01:33:24,836 --> 01:33:27,795
And I believe for the first time I...

979
01:33:29,354 --> 01:33:34,792
I’m just beginning to understand
what it’s all about,

980
01:33:36,511 --> 01:33:40,230
what I really am and what I really want.

981
01:33:40,350 --> 01:33:42,309
It’s a nice feeling.

982
01:33:51,186 --> 01:33:53,505
Come on in.

983
01:33:53,625 --> 01:33:56,423
Ace, excuse me. I hate to bother you.

984
01:33:56,543 --> 01:33:59,542
- I just got the news.
- You got what news?

985
01:33:59,663 --> 01:34:03,661
- I’m gettin’ shipped back.
- You’re being shipped back where?

986
01:34:03,781 --> 01:34:07,620
Stateside. I’ve been reassigned
to a new duty station.

987
01:34:09,659 --> 01:34:12,178
Well...

988
01:34:12,297 --> 01:34:14,657
- Did you tell Katsumi yet?
- No.

989
01:34:14,777 --> 01:34:17,375
Don’t tell her.
Maybe we can work something out.

990
01:34:17,496 --> 01:34:20,775
What reason did they give you for it?

991
01:34:20,895 --> 01:34:24,214
No reason. But I know what it is.

992
01:34:24,334 --> 01:34:28,572
Every guy on that list
is married to a Japanese girl.

993
01:34:32,291 --> 01:34:36,049
I’m sorry, Major.
There’s nothing you can do.

994
01:34:38,368 --> 01:34:43,406
We’re sending Kelly to the States
Thursday, and that’s that.

995
01:34:44,285 --> 01:34:46,965
What about his wife, Colonel?

996
01:34:47,085 --> 01:34:49,043
She stays here.

997
01:34:49,924 --> 01:34:53,683
He knew he couldn’t take her back
with him when he married her.

998
01:34:53,803 --> 01:34:56,361
- Didn’t you?
- That’s right.

999
01:34:57,761 --> 01:34:59,920
You’d be busting up his home, then.

1000
01:35:00,040 --> 01:35:02,400
I’m not busting up anything.

1001
01:35:04,079 --> 01:35:08,317
Though I admit Kelly’s been
a pain in my side for quite a while now.

1002
01:35:08,437 --> 01:35:12,555
Could you tell me why he didn’t have
the privilege of extending his tour of duty?

1003
01:35:12,675 --> 01:35:18,074
Don’t ask me, Major. There are lots
of reasons for these things.

1004
01:35:18,193 --> 01:35:23,671
Anyway, it is an order
and there’s nothing you can do about it,

1005
01:35:23,791 --> 01:35:27,189
even if you are a four-star general’s son.

1006
01:35:27,309 --> 01:35:29,269
Yeah, well...

1007
01:35:31,788 --> 01:35:38,026
Would it make any difference if I told you
my wife’s gonna have a baby?

1008
01:35:38,666 --> 01:35:41,025
That’s tough, I admit.

1009
01:35:42,984 --> 01:35:47,062
Colonel, under these circumstances,
don’t you think that you’d be able to

1010
01:35:47,182 --> 01:35:49,942
postpone this for a little while?

1011
01:35:50,061 --> 01:35:53,062
Maybe I could be transferred
back to Korea.

1012
01:35:53,181 --> 01:35:55,139
No, you’re going home.

1013
01:35:57,339 --> 01:36:00,578
All the boys on this list are going home.

1014
01:36:01,737 --> 01:36:05,415
- Where is your home?
- That house by the canal.

1015
01:36:06,495 --> 01:36:09,533
- I mean your real home.
- That house by the canal.

1016
01:36:09,654 --> 01:36:11,612
Yeah, all right.

1017
01:36:13,252 --> 01:36:17,650
I’ve taken all the insubordination
from you I intend to.

1018
01:36:17,770 --> 01:36:20,529
Now, you listen to me, wise guy.

1019
01:36:20,649 --> 01:36:25,008
That house by the canal
is off limits from now on.

1020
01:36:26,167 --> 01:36:28,687
Whole street’s off limits.

1021
01:36:28,807 --> 01:36:31,406
Do you want a court martial?

1022
01:36:31,526 --> 01:36:33,684
Does that mean I could stay in Japan?

1023
01:36:33,804 --> 01:36:37,963
You’re shipping outta here on Thursday.
And don’t you try to help him.

1024
01:36:40,203 --> 01:36:45,440
Remember that house by the canal
is off limits to all personnel.

1025
01:36:47,119 --> 01:36:50,998
Would you tell me just exactly
what you mean by that last remark?

1026
01:36:51,118 --> 01:36:54,316
That’s all I’m prepared
to say at the minute.

1027
01:36:54,436 --> 01:36:57,076
Except you watch your step.

1028
01:37:01,714 --> 01:37:05,792
I don’t know what else to tell you,
General. I’ve known this boy a long time.

1029
01:37:05,912 --> 01:37:10,550
If he has to go back without Katsumi,
he’s gonna be in trouble.

1030
01:37:10,671 --> 01:37:13,270
That’s about it. That’s it.

1031
01:37:13,390 --> 01:37:15,829
- What about his wife?
- I don’t know.

1032
01:37:15,949 --> 01:37:17,548
And the baby?

1033
01:37:19,508 --> 01:37:24,185
So the army lets them get married and
then forces them to desert their wives.

1034
01:37:24,305 --> 01:37:26,985
That’s not fair, Eileen.

1035
01:37:27,105 --> 01:37:30,463
A boy away from home
for the first time, lonesome,

1036
01:37:30,583 --> 01:37:33,062
often falls in love
with the first girl he touches,

1037
01:37:33,181 --> 01:37:36,061
in most cases with a girl from the streets.

1038
01:37:36,181 --> 01:37:42,020
It’s up to the service in some measure
to be fathers and mothers to these boys

1039
01:37:42,139 --> 01:37:44,977
and try to head off these marriages.

1040
01:37:45,097 --> 01:37:47,417
But after they’re married,
why send them home?

1041
01:37:47,537 --> 01:37:51,056
He’s being transferred to a new
duty station, along with many others.

1042
01:37:51,136 --> 01:37:55,775
Don’t ask me the reasons for changes
of duty. There are thousands of them.

1043
01:37:55,894 --> 01:37:59,733
But Lloyd said most of the men on this list
are married to Japanese girls.

1044
01:37:59,853 --> 01:38:04,691
- That can’t be just a coincidence.
- Why not? It could easily be.

1045
01:38:04,811 --> 01:38:10,208
Frankly, with some of these men,
I think they might welcome the transfer.

1046
01:38:10,328 --> 01:38:12,088
Why’s that, sir?

1047
01:38:12,208 --> 01:38:15,566
There have been unfortunate aftermaths
to many of these marriages.

1048
01:38:15,686 --> 01:38:18,046
Recriminations, regrets.

1049
01:38:19,325 --> 01:38:23,803
A boy gets married impulsively, then feels
caught, doesn’t know how to get out of it.

1050
01:38:23,923 --> 01:38:28,682
Change of duty gives them both
a chance to think it over, to cool off.

1051
01:38:28,802 --> 01:38:33,881
I don’t mean to imply that’s the reason
these men are being transferred but...

1052
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:39,598
well, the whole thing’s a messy business.

1053
01:38:41,438 --> 01:38:45,876
General Webster, there is no regret
in the case of Kelly and Katsumi.

1054
01:38:45,996 --> 01:38:48,115
You can have my word on that.

1055
01:38:48,234 --> 01:38:54,432
Lloyd, three officers came to me today
with identical requests for their men.

1056
01:38:54,552 --> 01:38:58,630
It’s not our policy to interfere with
decisions made by commanding officers.

1057
01:38:58,750 --> 01:39:04,469
The basic structure of the military service
would collapse if we did things like that.

1058
01:39:04,589 --> 01:39:08,027
Your father would understand that,
even if you don’t.

1059
01:39:08,147 --> 01:39:15,184
You’re asking me to make an exception of
Kelly when I’ve refused these other men?

1060
01:39:15,304 --> 01:39:17,943
I am gonna ask you to do that, sir.

1061
01:39:19,343 --> 01:39:24,102
You made an exception of me
when you brought me from Korea.

1062
01:39:24,982 --> 01:39:28,741
I’m afraid it’s a hopeless situation, Lloyd.

1063
01:39:33,058 --> 01:39:35,017
Well...

1064
01:39:36,257 --> 01:39:39,095
That’s the end of Joe Kelly.

1065
01:39:39,215 --> 01:39:42,534
You told me yourself that Kelly’s
past record was against him.

1066
01:39:42,654 --> 01:39:44,414
I couldn’t even use that.

1067
01:39:44,533 --> 01:39:47,132
Why does this mean
so much to you, Lloyd?

1068
01:39:49,092 --> 01:39:53,411
Kelly’s from my outfit, Mrs. Webster,
I was his best man,

1069
01:39:53,531 --> 01:39:57,449
and I’m planning to marry
a Japanese girl myself.

1070
01:40:00,928 --> 01:40:05,646
Come into the other room, Eileen. This is
something for your father to handle.

1071
01:40:05,765 --> 01:40:09,965
No, Mrs. Webster. I don’t think
this is anything for anybody to handle.

1072
01:40:15,522 --> 01:40:17,481
I’m sorry, Eileen.

1073
01:40:22,119 --> 01:40:24,958
Mrs. Webster. Good afternoon.

1074
01:40:31,436 --> 01:40:36,234
I don’t think I’ll ever love anyone again
as much as I love Lloyd.

1075
01:40:36,354 --> 01:40:39,953
But I’ll tell you something
that’s rather ironic.

1076
01:40:40,073 --> 01:40:43,232
I once asked Lloyd
if he ever felt like grabbing me

1077
01:40:43,352 --> 01:40:47,309
and hauling me off to a shack somewhere.

1078
01:40:47,430 --> 01:40:52,428
That’s just what he’s done, isn’t it?
Only it’s with somebody else.

1079
01:40:52,547 --> 01:40:55,626
Don’t go out, Eileen. Stay and talk.

1080
01:40:55,746 --> 01:40:59,664
I’m sorry, Mother. There’s only one
person I’d like to talk to at the moment.

1081
01:40:59,784 --> 01:41:02,624
And, oddly enough, he’s Japanese.

1082
01:41:06,582 --> 01:41:09,901
- Ace, I’ve been waiting for you.
- Kelly, listen.

1083
01:41:10,021 --> 01:41:14,499
I just came from General Webster’s
house. There’s a whole big mess there.

1084
01:41:14,619 --> 01:41:19,417
- No good, huh?
- No. He didn’t go for it.

1085
01:41:19,537 --> 01:41:23,616
Matter of fact, I think
I even messed it up a little.

1086
01:41:23,736 --> 01:41:25,736
That figures.

1087
01:41:25,855 --> 01:41:27,894
Did you tell Katsumi yet?

1088
01:41:29,293 --> 01:41:31,533
I’m chickening out fast.

1089
01:41:31,653 --> 01:41:35,212
Besides, she’s got her heart set
on something she planned for us tonight.

1090
01:41:35,332 --> 01:41:40,569
Wants us to take the train over to Osaka
and meet the girls at the puppet show.

1091
01:41:40,689 --> 01:41:42,649
Why spoil it?

1092
01:41:44,328 --> 01:41:48,606
Maybe I’ll tell her late tonight
when we’re alone.

1093
01:41:48,726 --> 01:41:52,924
Listen, Kelly, don’t give up on it.
I think there’s gonna be a way out of it.

1094
01:41:53,044 --> 01:41:55,404
You think so? I don’t.

1095
01:41:57,324 --> 01:41:59,963
- I’ll see you, Ace.
- Kelly-san.

1096
01:42:01,043 --> 01:42:04,800
Tell Katsumi we’ll be there with bells.

1097
01:42:04,920 --> 01:42:06,880
Were you able to help?

1098
01:42:09,919 --> 01:42:12,558
- No.
- How terrible.

1099
01:42:16,957 --> 01:42:20,234
I know it’s hard, honey,
but it’s not gonna last long.

1100
01:42:20,354 --> 01:42:24,913
The army’s gotta change that law
next year, or the next one.

1101
01:42:25,033 --> 01:42:27,991
It just has to be. I’m sure of it.

1102
01:42:29,831 --> 01:42:34,389
And, in fact, I’m so sure of it
that I went downtown today

1103
01:42:34,510 --> 01:42:39,588
and I signed some papers here that mean
that you and I are gonna get married.

1104
01:42:42,346 --> 01:42:45,586
- What’s the matter?
- We never spoke of marriage.

1105
01:42:45,706 --> 01:42:49,064
I know we didn’t, darling.
I know we didn’t.

1106
01:42:49,185 --> 01:42:55,702
I’ve been going round and round with that
every day for a long time.

1107
01:42:55,821 --> 01:43:00,220
I didn’t feel I could
speak about it until now.

1108
01:43:00,340 --> 01:43:02,299
But now I can.

1109
01:43:03,498 --> 01:43:06,697
Now, of course, I won’t be able
to take you back to America,

1110
01:43:06,817 --> 01:43:10,816
but they’re bound to change
that ridiculous law soon.

1111
01:43:10,935 --> 01:43:14,174
Until then I’m gonna stay here with you.

1112
01:43:15,614 --> 01:43:18,493
I’m not stuck in the air force. I can resign.

1113
01:43:18,613 --> 01:43:23,931
Course, I’m not trained to do
anything else, but I’d find something.

1114
01:43:25,130 --> 01:43:27,650
We never spoke of marriage.

1115
01:43:28,569 --> 01:43:32,089
I know we didn’t, darling,
but we’re speaking of it now.

1116
01:43:39,246 --> 01:43:42,563
Do you remember
the first night we talked?

1117
01:43:42,683 --> 01:43:47,242
I said there would be danger
of weakness when it is over.

1118
01:43:49,641 --> 01:43:52,361
Over? What are you talking about?

1119
01:43:55,240 --> 01:44:00,957
I’m tempted. With you, I could become
and woman and a mother,

1120
01:44:01,077 --> 01:44:03,037
and I could love you.

1121
01:44:04,596 --> 01:44:06,635
That’s right.

1122
01:44:06,756 --> 01:44:09,314
Do you think I haven’t thought about it?

1123
01:44:09,434 --> 01:44:14,553
Do you think I want to become a lonely
old woman who teaches dancing,

1124
01:44:14,673 --> 01:44:17,032
now that I have known you?

1125
01:44:18,471 --> 01:44:20,950
But it is no good.

1126
01:44:21,070 --> 01:44:26,508
- You must know it too.
- No. I don’t know anything of the kind.

1127
01:44:27,747 --> 01:44:31,226
The way you talk about
leaving the air force,

1128
01:44:31,346 --> 01:44:36,744
finding some pitiful way of earning living,
just to be here with your Japanese wife.

1129
01:44:36,863 --> 01:44:39,223
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

1130
01:44:41,941 --> 01:44:46,621
I think we’re too far into this thing
to be talking like that.

1131
01:44:46,740 --> 01:44:50,340
Matsubayashi has been kind to me, Lloyd.

1132
01:44:50,459 --> 01:44:54,858
- I am obligated to them.
- No, you ain’t. No, no.

1133
01:44:54,978 --> 01:44:56,977
You are obligated to me.

1134
01:44:58,257 --> 01:45:00,295
They are my life.

1135
01:45:00,415 --> 01:45:03,935
I would bring shame to them, disgrace.

1136
01:45:04,054 --> 01:45:06,094
Lloyd, you know what I mean.

1137
01:45:06,213 --> 01:45:09,732
Yeah, I think I’m beginning
to know what you mean.

1138
01:45:09,852 --> 01:45:13,370
I think you mean you simply don’t
love me enough to go on through with it.

1139
01:45:13,490 --> 01:45:17,968
That’s what you mean, don’t you? Why
don’t you just come on out and say it?

1140
01:45:18,089 --> 01:45:20,047
It is not what I mean.

1141
01:45:24,646 --> 01:45:30,084
I’m leaving for Tokyo in six days.
Matsubayashi are sending me.

1142
01:45:30,203 --> 01:45:32,322
You what?

1143
01:45:33,922 --> 01:45:38,081
With another troupe.
They have found out about us.

1144
01:45:39,120 --> 01:45:42,918
Any other girl they would have dismissed,
but because they like me,

1145
01:45:43,039 --> 01:45:47,438
because they feel I am important to them,
they are being lenient.

1146
01:45:48,435 --> 01:45:51,554
Well, I’m not gonna be lenient with you.

1147
01:45:51,675 --> 01:45:56,673
I want you to tell me why Matsubayashi
means more to you than I do.

1148
01:45:58,912 --> 01:46:04,310
Lloyd, there is something about myself
I have not told you.

1149
01:46:04,431 --> 01:46:07,549
I have no right to marry anyone.

1150
01:46:07,669 --> 01:46:10,668
My father was very poor.

1151
01:46:10,788 --> 01:46:15,906
To save his other children,
he was forced to sell one of his daughters.

1152
01:46:17,426 --> 01:46:21,945
The man from
the houses of Yoshiwara came to him.

1153
01:46:22,064 --> 01:46:27,262
Because I was the oldest,
he agreed I should go with him.

1154
01:46:29,541 --> 01:46:32,100
Your father sold you?

1155
01:46:32,220 --> 01:46:39,097
Yes, but I was saved from starting this life
by my best friend, Fumiko-san.

1156
01:46:41,816 --> 01:46:44,456
Her father paid money to free me.

1157
01:46:45,615 --> 01:46:48,654
Then she brought me to Matsubayashi.

1158
01:46:51,293 --> 01:46:57,531
There I not only earned my living,
I brought honor back to my family.

1159
01:47:00,490 --> 01:47:03,530
Matsubayashi has been kind to me.

1160
01:47:03,650 --> 01:47:06,128
They have trusted me.

1161
01:47:06,967 --> 01:47:11,526
I cannot leave them.
I cannot marry anyone.

1162
01:47:15,325 --> 01:47:17,283
Don’t you understand?

1163
01:47:23,881 --> 01:47:25,840
I don’t know.

1164
01:47:26,920 --> 01:47:30,278
I don’t know what to think.

1165
01:47:31,359 --> 01:47:36,956
I’ll kill you! You ever do anything like this
and I’ll kill you, you understand?

1166
01:47:37,076 --> 01:47:41,834
- Wait a minute. Just take it easy, now.
- Ace, look at this.

1167
01:47:43,074 --> 01:47:45,113
- It fell out of her bag.
- What is it?

1168
01:47:45,233 --> 01:47:49,832
She was gonna have it done tomorrow,
by that quack doctor down by the docks.

1169
01:47:49,951 --> 01:47:53,750
For eight bucks he slashes her eyelids
and sews ‘em back up again.

1170
01:47:53,870 --> 01:47:58,948
Lots of these stupid little jerks
have it done. She was gonna surprise me.

1171
01:47:59,068 --> 01:48:04,266
Then... then I have good eyes,
I fool everybody.

1172
01:48:04,386 --> 01:48:08,065
I look American, like Joe.

1173
01:48:08,184 --> 01:48:13,422
Hana-ogi, will you tell that stupid dame
I love her the way she is?

1174
01:48:13,542 --> 01:48:17,861
I don’t want her changed. Will you tell her
I love her mouth and her nose

1175
01:48:17,982 --> 01:48:21,699
and her ears and her eyes
just the way they are?

1176
01:48:21,821 --> 01:48:26,899
Tell her if she ever does
anything like that, I’ll...

1177
01:48:27,018 --> 01:48:30,657
I want him be proud of me.

1178
01:48:30,777 --> 01:48:32,416
I’m sorry.

1179
01:48:32,535 --> 01:48:35,335
If you want him to be proud of you,
quit this stuff.

1180
01:48:35,455 --> 01:48:41,051
You’re making him very unhappy.
Tell him you’re not gonna do it any more.

1181
01:48:41,171 --> 01:48:43,771
- Tell him that.
- Joe.

1182
01:48:45,611 --> 01:48:47,330
I’m so sorry.

1183
01:48:50,329 --> 01:48:53,088
We’re gonna forget about that.

1184
01:48:53,209 --> 01:48:58,486
I thought we were gonna have a fish fry,
have some fun and dancing and yelling.

1185
01:48:58,606 --> 01:49:01,245
And what do I find?
So what’s gonna happen to us?

1186
01:49:01,365 --> 01:49:03,444
- Puppet show.
- We had a surprise.

1187
01:49:03,564 --> 01:49:06,563
- You like?
- Sure I do. I’ve been looking forward to it.

1188
01:49:06,683 --> 01:49:09,803
- Everybody tonight?
- Yeah.

1189
01:49:14,441 --> 01:49:16,400
We will be late.

1190
01:49:23,596 --> 01:49:25,076
Look.

1191
01:49:25,196 --> 01:49:27,915
The lover is leaving the city.

1192
01:49:28,035 --> 01:49:29,994
Walk to the wood.

1193
01:50:05,821 --> 01:50:09,419
Lloyd, don’t think of anything now.

1194
01:50:10,418 --> 01:50:12,578
Watch the play.

1195
01:50:12,698 --> 01:50:14,657
It’s a tender story.

1196
01:50:22,614 --> 01:50:26,372
When gong sound, it is dawn,

1197
01:50:26,492 --> 01:50:31,290
and then she will bind her body.

1198
01:50:32,211 --> 01:50:33,650
Bind her body?

1199
01:50:33,770 --> 01:50:39,768
So that she will not fall in an ugly position
of dishonor when she dies.

1200
01:50:39,888 --> 01:50:42,725
- When she dies?
- Yes.

1201
01:50:59,440 --> 01:51:05,398
It is custom for lovers to die together
when they can no longer face life.

1202
01:51:15,075 --> 01:51:17,434
It is so beautiful.

1203
01:51:18,154 --> 01:51:21,352
Beautiful? They’re gonna die, aren’t they?

1204
01:51:21,472 --> 01:51:25,989
They will live in another world
on a beautiful lake,

1205
01:51:26,109 --> 01:51:29,188
floating always together.

1206
01:51:29,308 --> 01:51:31,268
Like water lily.

1207
01:51:33,826 --> 01:51:35,787
Sure.

1208
01:52:53,757 --> 01:52:57,397
" Kelly-san! Kelly-san! Kelly-san!

1209
01:53:06,593 --> 01:53:10,831
Something about soldiers
going through the house.

1210
01:53:14,270 --> 01:53:17,430
- That’s the MPs, boy.
- What happened? What’s wrong?

1211
01:53:17,549 --> 01:53:20,188
- What happened?
- Get in the car.

1212
01:53:21,948 --> 01:53:26,146
- Please tell me.
- Go to Matsubayashi. I’ll tell you later.

1213
01:53:26,266 --> 01:53:27,225
Matsubayashi.

1214
01:53:30,223 --> 01:53:32,423
Hey, Ed, look.

1215
01:53:47,178 --> 01:53:49,137
Look at that.

1216
01:53:51,892 --> 01:53:54,930
- You’re Major Gruver, aren’t you?
- That’s right.

1217
01:53:55,051 --> 01:53:57,729
You’ll have to come with us.
General Webster’s orders.

1218
01:53:57,849 --> 01:54:00,130
What right do you have
to board up this house?

1219
01:54:00,249 --> 01:54:02,448
He won’t be needing it. He’s shipping out.

1220
01:54:02,568 --> 01:54:04,287
Joe!

1221
01:54:04,407 --> 01:54:06,366
Come on, Major.

1222
01:54:08,207 --> 01:54:10,564
You’ll hear from me, Kelly.

1223
01:54:23,360 --> 01:54:26,118
Come on, kid.
We’ll get in through the garden.

1224
01:54:26,238 --> 01:54:28,918
I got something to tell you.

1225
01:54:50,950 --> 01:54:54,227
You were seen in public with her tonight,
violating orders.

1226
01:54:54,347 --> 01:54:57,785
This has given me the right
to put you under arrest.

1227
01:54:57,905 --> 01:55:01,344
And for your own sake,
I think I better do it.

1228
01:55:01,464 --> 01:55:04,463
Well? Have you anything to say?

1229
01:55:06,423 --> 01:55:13,100
Just as soon as I’m out of this, I’m gonna
be married and have a house of my own.

1230
01:55:13,220 --> 01:55:17,338
I’m afraid not.
I’m sorry, Lloyd, but it’s all settled.

1231
01:55:17,459 --> 01:55:20,937
The supervisor of the Matsubayashi
came to see me tonight.

1232
01:55:21,057 --> 01:55:26,097
The girl goes to Tokyo and you fly to
Randolph Field the day after tomorrow.

1233
01:55:26,217 --> 01:55:28,895
Here are your orders.

1234
01:55:29,014 --> 01:55:32,853
Until that time, you’re under house arrest.

1235
01:55:32,973 --> 01:55:37,612
You’re not to leave your quarters
until further notice.

1236
01:55:41,249 --> 01:55:44,648
I’m doing this because I feel
you’re not responsible at the moment.

1237
01:55:44,768 --> 01:55:48,207
After all, I’ve known your father for years.

1238
01:55:52,765 --> 01:55:55,125
Well, that’s all.

1239
01:56:28,672 --> 01:56:30,632
Mike.

1240
01:56:30,751 --> 01:56:33,231
- Did you see her?
- I couldn’t get near the place.

1241
01:56:33,351 --> 01:56:36,430
They’ve really clamped down.
I couldn’t even see Fumiko-san.

1242
01:56:36,550 --> 01:56:39,309
I’ve got to see her.
I’m being shipped out tomorrow.

1243
01:56:39,428 --> 01:56:41,908
- Major Gruver.
- What is it?

1244
01:56:42,028 --> 01:56:44,987
- Would you do something for us?
- What do you want?

1245
01:56:45,106 --> 01:56:48,065
- Airman Kelly’s disappeared.
- That’s impossible.

1246
01:56:48,186 --> 01:56:50,545
- I was with him just last night.
- We know.

1247
01:56:50,665 --> 01:56:55,662
A special plane came through and
Colonel Crawford told us to get him on it.

1248
01:56:55,782 --> 01:57:00,701
I took him to the airport at 12.50. When
the plane took off, Kelly wasn’t on it.

1249
01:57:00,821 --> 01:57:05,418
- We figured you might know where he is.
- His house has been boarded up.

1250
01:57:05,538 --> 01:57:06,498
We know.

1251
01:57:06,617 --> 01:57:10,336
Neighbors won’t talk to us.
We figure maybe they’re hiding him.

1252
01:57:10,456 --> 01:57:13,696
They’ll talk with you, Major.
Would you help us?

1253
01:57:13,816 --> 01:57:17,574
Would you give me one good reason
why I should?

1254
01:57:18,494 --> 01:57:21,773
We figured we’d give him a break.
We haven’t reported him yet.

1255
01:57:21,893 --> 01:57:27,971
If we get him on another plane, we might
not have to turn him in for desertion.

1256
01:57:28,091 --> 01:57:30,049
- Desertion?
- Yes, sir.

1257
01:57:33,449 --> 01:57:35,408
Well...

1258
01:57:36,208 --> 01:57:39,687
- I’ll go with you in a minute.
- Major.

1259
01:57:39,806 --> 01:57:42,086
The neighbors won’t talk
if they see an MP.

1260
01:57:42,205 --> 01:57:45,044
- I’ll go with him.
- Thank you, sir.

1261
01:58:42,903 --> 01:58:44,862
Kelly?

1262
01:58:47,222 --> 01:58:49,180
It’s Gruver out here.

1263
01:58:51,300 --> 01:58:53,259
I think he’s in there.

1264
01:58:54,658 --> 01:58:56,617
Kelly?

1265
01:58:57,778 --> 01:58:59,736
I’m goin’ on in.

1266
01:59:12,931 --> 01:59:14,891
Kelly?

1267
01:59:21,088 --> 01:59:23,047
Kelly?

1268
01:59:28,604 --> 01:59:31,164
Kelly? You in there?

1269
01:59:53,795 --> 01:59:55,754
Oh, my God!

1270
01:59:59,153 --> 02:00:01,113
Oh, my...

1271
02:00:20,466 --> 02:00:22,425
Oh...

1272
02:00:28,023 --> 02:00:30,181
I’ll call the police, Ace.

1273
02:00:46,936 --> 02:00:48,895
Oh, God!

1274
02:01:22,802 --> 02:01:25,841
" Sayonara, Kelly-san.

1275
02:01:29,160 --> 02:01:32,959
Sayonara, Katsumi-san.

1276
02:01:42,474 --> 02:01:46,954
Sayonara, my Lloyd-san.

1277
02:02:21,541 --> 02:02:24,779
" Go home! Go home!

1278
02:02:30,138 --> 02:02:34,776
Ace, there’s no police around.
We better get outta here.

1279
02:02:35,456 --> 02:02:37,374
Hey, look.

1280
02:02:44,371 --> 02:02:46,931
Doesn’t look too good, boy.

1281
02:02:52,249 --> 02:02:54,048
Come on, take it easy.

1282
02:03:25,916 --> 02:03:27,955
We’re gettin’ help, Ace.

1283
02:03:40,551 --> 02:03:43,790
- You OK, boy?
- I’m fine. You all right?

1284
02:03:43,910 --> 02:03:45,310
Yeah.

1285
02:03:45,430 --> 02:03:49,748
I’m gonna... I want you
to take care of everything, will you?

1286
02:03:49,868 --> 02:03:52,268
Yeah, I’ll get it.

1287
02:03:52,387 --> 02:03:54,347
I’ll see you later.

1288
02:04:39,609 --> 02:04:41,808
- Where’s Hana-ogi?
- Hana-ogi is not here.

1289
02:04:41,928 --> 02:04:45,006
- I know she’s here.
- She is on her way Tokyo.

1290
02:04:45,125 --> 02:04:48,525
- She wasn’t going till next week.
- She went today.

1291
02:04:48,645 --> 02:04:53,683
- I don’t believe you.
- Major Gruver! It’s forbidden to go in.

1292
02:05:38,707 --> 02:05:40,665
Hana-ogi?

1293
02:05:49,903 --> 02:05:53,021
Hana-ogi? Hana-ogi?

1294
02:05:53,580 --> 02:05:55,541
Hana-ogi?

1295
02:06:04,737 --> 02:06:06,695
Hana-ogi?

1296
02:06:12,933 --> 02:06:15,133
- Gruver-san!
- Where’s Hana-ogi?

1297
02:06:15,212 --> 02:06:16,971
- She’s gone.
- Where’s her room?

1298
02:06:17,092 --> 02:06:20,450
- She’s gone.
- Listen, where’s her room?

1299
02:06:20,570 --> 02:06:22,370
Come here.

1300
02:06:25,170 --> 02:06:27,608
Hana-ogi really gone, Major.

1301
02:06:27,728 --> 02:06:29,688
I don’t believe you.

1302
02:06:30,327 --> 02:06:32,286
Hana-ogi?

1303
02:06:37,725 --> 02:06:42,403
I give you my word.
You go now too, Major.

1304
02:06:42,523 --> 02:06:44,762
It’s over.

1305
02:06:44,883 --> 02:06:47,601
Leave me alone a minute, will you?

1306
02:07:02,914 --> 02:07:06,314
The hoodlums who attacked you
weren’t all your Japanese neighbors.

1307
02:07:06,434 --> 02:07:09,073
They were troublemakers
sent to your street

1308
02:07:09,193 --> 02:07:11,912
to create an incident specifically with you.

1309
02:07:12,031 --> 02:07:15,071
If you’re important to those who hate us,

1310
02:07:15,190 --> 02:07:18,549
don’t you see
how important you are to us?

1311
02:07:20,549 --> 02:07:23,707
Do you understand any of this, Lloyd?

1312
02:07:25,427 --> 02:07:27,466
I know how you feel.

1313
02:07:27,585 --> 02:07:28,986
It was...

1314
02:07:29,106 --> 02:07:34,742
It was dreadful about your friend Kelly
and... and his wife.

1315
02:07:36,743 --> 02:07:39,100
It must be hard to take.

1316
02:07:41,101 --> 02:07:45,339
And I... I hate to tell you something else,

1317
02:07:45,459 --> 02:07:49,578
because it’s almost too grotesque...

1318
02:07:52,377 --> 02:07:55,256
almost unforgivable
in your eyes, I imagine.

1319
02:07:55,375 --> 02:08:01,893
I got word today that there’s a law
being passed in a month or two

1320
02:08:02,013 --> 02:08:05,332
that will make it possible
for men like Kelly

1321
02:08:05,452 --> 02:08:09,491
to take their Japanese brides
back to the States.

1322
02:08:13,448 --> 02:08:18,886
- That can’t be true, General.
- Well, it happens to be true, Lloyd.

1323
02:08:23,325 --> 02:08:28,363
Listen, how do you get the guts
to come here and tell me that?

1324
02:08:28,483 --> 02:08:32,082
It takes time to get laws passed, Lloyd.

1325
02:08:32,202 --> 02:08:36,720
And a lot of people have died in this world
needlessly waiting for them.

1326
02:08:36,840 --> 02:08:40,798
It’s harder to take
when it hits you personally.

1327
02:08:43,158 --> 02:08:45,077
Lloyd...

1328
02:08:45,197 --> 02:08:47,756
You’re lost. You’re confused.

1329
02:08:49,195 --> 02:08:52,913
Don’t you think it’s time you got back
to the mainstream of your life?

1330
02:08:53,033 --> 02:08:57,390
Back to your roots,
what you were born for and raised for.

1331
02:08:57,511 --> 02:09:04,349
You’ll feel better about everything when
you get back home, back to your work.

1332
02:09:04,469 --> 02:09:07,267
I appreciate you coming over, General.

1333
02:09:46,893 --> 02:09:49,251
Take me to the airport, Mike.

1334
02:09:54,730 --> 02:09:56,809
That must be him.

1335
02:09:56,929 --> 02:10:02,368
- Hold it so we can get a picture, General.
- Where would you like me?

1336
02:10:02,847 --> 02:10:04,806
Smile, please.

1337
02:10:10,245 --> 02:10:14,084
- Bill, isn’t that Ace Gruver?
- Looks like him.

1338
02:10:16,722 --> 02:10:18,840
Sir.

1339
02:10:18,961 --> 02:10:21,200
Aren’t you Major Gruver? Ace Gruver?

1340
02:10:21,320 --> 02:10:23,918
- That’s right.
- We’re from the "Stars and Stripes."

1341
02:10:24,039 --> 02:10:28,397
- What are you doing in Tokyo?
- I’m just passing through, boys.

1342
02:10:28,518 --> 02:10:31,796
- Just seeing the sights, huh?
- That’s right. I’m in a hurry.

1343
02:10:31,916 --> 02:10:36,555
- Do you mind if I excuse myself? Sorry.
- You’re excused.

1344
02:12:20,636 --> 02:12:22,796
It’s Gruver! Gruver-san!

1345
02:12:47,946 --> 02:12:49,265
Lloyd-san.

1346
02:12:50,785 --> 02:12:52,544
Hello.

1347
02:13:10,657 --> 02:13:12,896
Hello, Hana-ogi.

1348
02:13:15,096 --> 02:13:18,614
I’m goin’ back to America on Friday,

1349
02:13:18,734 --> 02:13:23,572
and I probably won’t
get back in Japan again.

1350
02:13:26,732 --> 02:13:29,490
And before I go, there was just...

1351
02:13:30,809 --> 02:13:33,369
just one thing I wanted to know.

1352
02:13:35,727 --> 02:13:38,886
You remember one time you said to me...

1353
02:13:40,846 --> 02:13:46,723
that you could love me
and be a wife and a mother?

1354
02:13:48,162 --> 02:13:50,481
I remember.

1355
02:13:52,240 --> 02:13:54,200
You said that since you’d known me,

1356
02:13:54,320 --> 02:13:59,678
you’d been afraid of being
a lonely old woman teaching dancing.

1357
02:13:59,798 --> 02:14:02,517
Remember that?

1358
02:14:02,637 --> 02:14:04,796
I remember.

1359
02:14:05,516 --> 02:14:09,555
Did you mean that
when you said it, Hana-ogi?

1360
02:14:10,474 --> 02:14:14,193
I meant it. It is already happening.

1361
02:14:14,313 --> 02:14:18,671
Life has gone out of my work, out of me.

1362
02:14:18,791 --> 02:14:21,550
Lloyd, please go now.

1363
02:14:21,670 --> 02:14:24,829
This will only bring pain and trouble.

1364
02:14:26,989 --> 02:14:30,866
Hana-ogi, you and I
are gonna have more trouble

1365
02:14:30,986 --> 02:14:33,505
than we ever thought
of having in our whole lives

1366
02:14:33,625 --> 02:14:37,664
unless you are absolutely
honest with yourself.

1367
02:14:38,943 --> 02:14:43,302
Please, Lloyd,
can’t we talk about this later?

1368
02:14:43,422 --> 02:14:49,180
No. There’s isn’t gonna be any later.
There’s only gonna be right now.

1369
02:14:51,059 --> 02:14:53,498
Excuse me, mother. Excuse me.

1370
02:14:57,417 --> 02:15:00,336
I must return this robe.

1371
02:15:00,456 --> 02:15:04,935
I wanna know -
do you love me or don’t you?

1372
02:15:06,093 --> 02:15:11,612
Because if you don’t, then I’m gonna
have to find a way to live with it.

1373
02:15:11,732 --> 02:15:14,250
- And if you do...
- Please, Lloyd.

1374
02:15:15,970 --> 02:15:18,328
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

1375
02:15:21,408 --> 02:15:25,646
I don’t want you to tell me
anything more or anything less

1376
02:15:25,766 --> 02:15:29,245
than you feel
in the very deepest part of you.

1377
02:15:29,365 --> 02:15:35,603
Because what you answer to me now
is gonna affect us for the rest of our lives.

1378
02:15:36,442 --> 02:15:40,202
Do you love me, Hana-ogi,
or don’t you love me?

1379
02:15:42,921 --> 02:15:45,639
I’m so frightened and confused.

1380
02:15:45,759 --> 02:15:49,478
I cannot think.
I cannot even understand your thinking.

1381
02:15:49,597 --> 02:15:55,755
I’m not thinking. For the first time
in my life I’m not thinking and I don’t care.

1382
02:15:55,875 --> 02:15:57,834
But we must do the right thing.

1383
02:15:57,953 --> 02:16:00,353
What are you talking about,
the right thing?

1384
02:16:00,473 --> 02:16:03,432
We been wasting two good lives
trying to do the right thing -

1385
02:16:03,552 --> 02:16:07,271
the right thing for Matsubayashi,
the right thing for my father,

1386
02:16:07,391 --> 02:16:11,310
the right thing for the military,
the right thing for Japanese tradition,

1387
02:16:11,430 --> 02:16:14,469
the right thing for the great white race.

1388
02:16:14,589 --> 02:16:19,827
- But we have duties and obligations.
- We do have duties and obligations.

1389
02:16:19,947 --> 02:16:23,025
The first obligation we have
is to love each other,

1390
02:16:23,145 --> 02:16:26,744
to become man and wife
and raise some clean, sweet children,

1391
02:16:26,864 --> 02:16:29,704
and give them the very best
that we know how.

1392
02:16:29,824 --> 02:16:34,981
And if we don’t meet that obligation,
we ain’t gonna be any good to anybody.

1393
02:16:35,101 --> 02:16:39,738
We live in different worlds,
come from different races.

1394
02:16:41,779 --> 02:16:45,136
Honey, I want you to be my wife.

1395
02:16:46,736 --> 02:16:50,455
But what would happen to our children?
What would they be?

1396
02:16:50,575 --> 02:16:54,413
What would they be?
They’d be half-Japanese, half-American.

1397
02:16:54,533 --> 02:16:57,292
They’d be half-yellow and half-white.

1398
02:16:57,412 --> 02:17:00,171
They’d be half you, they’d be half me.

1399
02:17:00,292 --> 02:17:03,610
That’s all they’re gonna be.

1400
02:17:15,166 --> 02:17:18,404
Hana-ogi, I want you
to come with me now.

1401
02:17:19,563 --> 02:17:24,242
I want you to come with me now
down to the American consulate.

1402
02:17:24,362 --> 02:17:27,281
Here in Tokyo. We’re gonna start
filling out those papers.

1403
02:17:27,401 --> 02:17:32,959
We’ve only got a few days to get
this whole thing done and out of the way.

1404
02:17:40,797 --> 02:17:42,756
Will you come?

1405
02:17:52,712 --> 02:17:55,271
I’m gonna wait for you outside.

1406
02:18:23,939 --> 02:18:26,018
Did I tell you they’d be here?

1407
02:18:26,138 --> 02:18:30,536
- Look at this crowd.
- Look who’s here. Our rivals.

1408
02:18:30,656 --> 02:18:36,215
You guys heard about it too?
No secrets. No secrets in this country.

1409
02:18:41,293 --> 02:18:43,971
Major, what a coincidence.

1410
02:18:44,091 --> 02:18:46,251
You got a story for us, sir?

1411
02:18:47,171 --> 02:18:49,250
No, as a matter of fact, I don’t.

1412
02:18:49,369 --> 02:18:53,008
- You’re not gonna try to deny it, are you?
- Deny what?

1413
02:18:53,129 --> 02:18:55,647
The story.
Why won’t you give us the story?

1414
02:18:55,767 --> 02:18:59,046
- You’re big news now, sir.
- I don’t know what you’re talking about.

1415
02:19:01,485 --> 02:19:04,524
Here’s Hana-ogi. Maybe she’ll talk.

1416
02:19:20,318 --> 02:19:24,117
Come on, Hana-ogi.
That’s not fair. What did you say?

1417
02:19:24,237 --> 02:19:29,434
It is very difficult for a Japanese woman
to speak in public.

1418
02:19:29,554 --> 02:19:32,273
I have never done so.

1419
02:19:32,393 --> 02:19:34,833
But perhaps now it is the time.

1420
02:19:36,192 --> 02:19:40,431
Major Gruver has asked me
to be his... his wife.

1421
02:19:43,990 --> 02:19:48,947
He knows there are many people in
this country who will be disturbed by this.

1422
02:19:49,068 --> 02:19:51,787
I know my people will be shocked too.

1423
02:19:51,907 --> 02:19:56,945
But I hope they will learn to understand
and someday approve.

1424
02:19:58,185 --> 02:20:02,863
We are not afraid,
because we know this is right.

1425
02:20:02,983 --> 02:20:05,462
I hope I can continue as a dancer

1426
02:20:05,582 --> 02:20:11,019
and I hope when I am old,
I will be able to teach children to dance.

1427
02:20:12,099 --> 02:20:14,818
My own children.

1428
02:20:14,938 --> 02:20:17,937
Major, the big brass are gonna
yell their heads off.

1429
02:20:18,057 --> 02:20:24,614
The Japanese aren’t gonna like it either.
Have you got anything to say to them, sir?

1430
02:20:24,733 --> 02:20:25,813
Yeah.

1431
02:20:27,100 --> 02:20:29,238
Tell ‘em we said “sayonara”.


